---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 253
Tags:
  - Combat-Action=Judgement=The Round of Existence
By: St Catherine of Siena
---
This fire does not consume, because the damned, however much torment
they endure, never lose their being. I tell thee, they ask for death,
but they cannot obtain it, because they cannot lose being. They do
indeed lose the being of grace by their sin, but natural being, never.
